Name: MC_DIS_PS
Summary: MC DIS analysis for Breit-frame shower-sensitive and particle-level spin-correlation observables
Status: UNVALIDATED
Authors:
 - Andreas Papaefstathiou <apapaefs@kennesaw.edu> (modified)

Options:
 - JETINPUT=FULL,HARDPARTONS,TOP2PARTONS,TOP3PARTONS
 - DISMODE=NC,CC

RunInfo: Suitable for DIS.
NumEvents: 1000
PtCuts: [0]
Beams: [[p+, e-], [p+, e+]]
Description:
  Analysis of DIS Breit-frame dijet observables together with shower-sensitive
  jet observables. The baseline control histograms match MC_DIS_BREIT, while
  the additional histograms probe accepted extra radiation and current-
  hemisphere particle-level spin-correlation structure after the standard
  dijet selection.
  The DIS event selection uses 49 < Q^2 < 2500 GeV^2 together with
  0.2 < y < 0.6.
  The JETINPUT option selects either the full DIS final state (FULL, default),
  only final-state q/g partons from the Rivet DIS final state (HARDPARTONS),
  the hardest 2 final-state q/g partons from the Rivet DIS final state
  (TOP2PARTONS), or the hardest 3 such partons (TOP3PARTONS) before
  clustering in the Breit frame.
  Particle-level observables are constructed from visible stable particles in
  the Breit-frame current hemisphere, excluding the scattered lepton.
NeedsCrossSection: yes
